						               													<description>Anludim is a familial card combinations game in a magic universe. This game is about matching cards to create combinations (straight, flush, pair, three of a kind, four of a kind) to attract the attention of the teachers and get a lot of magical items.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cards are from 1 to 13 in 5 colors. The cards are dual (2 different numbers and colors on a card) and you can use the orientation of your choice in order to form combinations. Each teacher is tied to a combination. At your turn you have to play one mandatory action : play cards (straight, flush&amp;hellip;) or draw. You can also play a bonus action : put an item back to the general supply to draw one card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of your turn you get one magical item for each teacher in front of you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You play turn after turn until one of two events occurs :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1/ you empty 3 stacks of magical items, you count points of the magical items and the higher score gets to level up your coven.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2/ you get one item of each type, no matter the points of the items, you level up your coven.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to level up twice his coven wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
